Package swervelib.simulation.ironmaple.simulation.gamepieces

Interface GamePiece

All Known Implementing Classes:
CrescendoNoteOnField, GamePieceOnFieldSimulation, GamePieceProjectile, NoteOnFly, ReefscapeAlgaeOnField, ReefscapeAlgaeOnFly, ReefscapeCoralAlgaeStack, ReefscapeCoralOnField, ReefscapeCoralOnFly
public interface GamePiece

Interface for all Game pieces.

This class contains basic functions all game pieces will have so that game pieces of different types can be used interchangeably in collision detection.

    • getVelocity3dMPS

      Translation3d getVelocity3dMPS()

      Gives the velocity of the game piece.

      For grounded game pieces the z access velocity does not exist and so will be set to 0 automatically.
      Returns:
      The velocity of the game piece as a Translation3d.

    • isGrounded

      boolean isGrounded()

      Gives wether or not the piece is "grounded".

      A grounded piece is likely a child of GamePieceOnFieldSimulation while a non grounded piece is likely a child ofGamePieceProjectile.
      Returns:
      wether or not the piece is grounded.
